notes.text: I rang Java to confirm his order. He confirmed an order for 16 solar panels for his store in Burlington. He amended his order for the store in Salem from 12 to 24 due to an unprecedented demand for eco products.

contact.background: I met Jane at the annuall Eco Conference in Florida. Her company currently provides solar panels (along with a lot of other stuff) to the State Goverments of California, Nevada, Oregon, Arizona and Utah for capital building projects. Her current supplier is crazy expensive! I've asked to be able to tender for their next order.

notes.author: Cillian M.
notes.text: Called Jane today to discuss the possibility of us doing business together. She requires board approval before changing suppliers so requested a company prospectus. She did sound positive though

notes.author: Cillian M.
notes.text: I called Jane to confirm that she had received our perspectus. She mentioned how impressed she was with our competitive pricing structures. She will be bringing this to the board on 02/17 at the next board meeting. She promised to contact me after.

notes.text:
Emailed Jane for details on their sp requirements. They required 250 solar panels by April 30th.
They want all tenders in by March 31st.
